<?php

namespace App\Services;

class SchemaDictionary
{
    public static function get(): string
    {
        return <<<EOT
===========================
Table: invoice_details
Stores the header information of invoices.
Relationships:
- invoice_details.id → invoice_items_detail.invoice_id (one-to-many)
- invoice_details.id → paymentDetails.invoice_id (one-to-many)

Columns:
- id: PK, Unique invoice ID
- invoice_date: Date of invoice creation
- customer_name: Full name of the customer
- customer_id: Internal reference ID for the customer
- customer_email: Email ID of the customer
- is_member: Membership flag (Enum: 'no'=0, 'yes'=1)
- company: Customer company (if applicable)
- sales_clerk: Sales clerk handling the transaction
- commission_clerk: Commissionable clerk
- resource: Resource/staff/asset linked to invoice (trainer, therapist, etc.)
- pos_terminal: POS terminal identifier (string)
- pos_terminal_id: POS terminal numeric ID
- retail_discount: Total retail discount applied
- tax: Total tax applied
- total_amount: Grand total of the invoice
- franchise: Franchise name
- franchise_id: Franchise unique ID
- provider: Provider entity under franchise
- provider_id: Provider unique ID
- location: Location/branch/store name
- location_id: Location unique ID
- parent_invoice_id: Reference to original invoice (for refunds/linked invoices)
- invoice_number: Human-readable invoice number
- due_date: Due date for payment
- status: Invoice status (Paid, Pending, Refunded, etc.)
- notes: Additional notes or comments
- created_at: Record creation timestamp
- updated_at: Record last update timestamp

===========================
Table: invoice_items_detail
Stores line-item details for each invoice (products, services, packages, etc.)
Relationships:
- invoice_items_detail.invoice_id → invoice_details.id (many items per invoice)

Columns:
- id: PK, Unique identifier for the invoice item row
- invoice_id: FK → invoice_details.id
- item_type: Type of item (product, service, package, membership, etc.)
- item_type_id: Internal reference ID for the item type
- category: High-level product/service category (e.g., Fitness, Supplements)
- subcategory: Subcategory for further classification
- brand: Brand name if applicable
- department: Department responsible
- SKU: Stock Keeping Unit code
- UPC: Universal Product Code (barcode identifier)
- item_id: Internal unique ID for the item
- item_name: Human-readable name of the item
- COGS: Cost of Goods Sold for the item
- Commission: Commission percentage applied (decimal)
- co_feat_tax: Additional feature/facility tax
- guest_pass_discount: Discount applied due to guest pass
- membership_discount: Discount applied due to membership
- package_discount: Discount applied for package purchase
- refund_amount: Refund issued against this line item
- refund_co_feat_tax: Refund for feature tax
- refund_tax: Tax refunded for this item
- quantity: Number of units purchased
- unit_price: Selling price per unit
- discount_value: Direct discount value applied
- discount_amount: Calculated discount amount in currency
- tax_rate: Tax rate applied to this item
- total_price: Final total after tax/discounts
- created_at: Record creation timestamp
- updated_at: Record last update timestamp

===========================
Table: paymentDetails
Stores payment transaction details against invoices.
Relationships:
- paymentDetails.invoice_id → invoice_details.id (many payments per invoice)

Columns:
- id: PK, Unique payment record ID
- franchise: Franchise name
- franchise_id: Franchise unique ID
- provider: Provider name
- provider_id: Provider unique ID
- location: Location/branch/store name
- location_id: Location unique ID
- invoice_id: FK → invoice_details.id
- pos_terminal: POS terminal identifier (string)
- pos_terminal_id: POS terminal numeric ID
- payment_date: Date of payment
- amount_paid: Amount paid by customer
- payment_method: Method of payment (Cash, Card, Online, Wallet, etc.)
- refund_amount: Refund issued for this payment
- notes: Notes for this payment (transaction ID, remarks)
- created_at: Record creation timestamp
- updated_at: Record last update timestamp
EOT;
    }
}

